import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data = data.sort_values(by='total', ascending=False)
    ax = plt.bar(data['region'], data['total'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income across different regions?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['group'] = pd.Categorical(data['group'], categories=['<10000', '10000 to 14999', '15000 to 24999', '25000 to 34999', '35000 to 49999', '50000 to 74999', '75000 to 99999', '100000 to 149999', '150000 to 199999', '200000 or more'], ordered=True)
    data = data.sort_values('group')
    data['income'] = data['total'] * data['pct']
    data = data.groupby('group').sum()
    data['average_income'] = data['income'] / data['total']
    ax = data['average_income'].plot(kind='bar')
    ax.set_xlabel('Income Group')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Income')
    ax.set_title('What is the average income for each income group?')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    for i, v in enumerate(data['average_income']):
        ax.text(i, v, f'{v:.2f}', ha='center', va='bottom')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    data['group'] = pd.Categorical(data['group'], categories=['<10000', '10000 to 14999', '15000 to 24999', '25000 to 34999', '35000 to 49999', '50000 to 74999', '75000 to 99999', '100000 to 149999', '150000 to 199999', '200000 or more'], ordered=True)

    ax.set_ylabel('Region')

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    regions = data['region'].unique()
    for region in regions:
        region_data = data[data['region'] == region]
        plt.hist(region_data['total'], alpha=0.5, label=region)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Total Income')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income for each region?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
